Prysm is a Go implementation of Ethereum Serenity protocol as detailed by its
official specification. It contains a full beacon node implementation as well
as a validator client for participating in blockchain consensus.

Prysm utilizes the best-in-class tools for production servers and
interprocess communication, using Google's gRPC library, BoltDB as an
optimized, persistent, key-value store, and libp2p by Protocol Labs
for all peer-to-peer networking.
